The paper focuses on learning effective attention mechanisms for multimodal data in vision-and-language tasks, which are typically studied in computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) fields. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a deep neural network architecture, which involves training and optimization techniques that are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) research, suggesting cs.AI as another likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates its proposed model on multiple datasets, indicating a focus on performance evaluation and comparison, which is a common theme in the machine learning (ML) and computational linguistics (CL) fields, making cs.LG and cs.MM also likely sub-categories.
